==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[tholia]], Old Saxon [[þolon]], Old High German [[dolon|dolōn]], Old Norse [[þola]], Gothic [[𐌸𐌿𐌻𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /θolian/

===Verb===
'''þolian''' (class 2 weak: '''þolaþ''' ‘he suffers’, '''þolode''' ‘he suffered’, '''þolodon''' ‘they suffered’, '''ġeþolod''' past participle)
# to [[suffer]], [[endure]]

